race.comment: MAGNETIC CHESS (9) had trialled up nicely ahead of the debut, when she was $2.60 into $2 but was trapped wide throughout. While beaten 2.5 lengths, she boxed on courageously and with a better run in transit here she can go one better. The step up to 1400m shouldn't be an issue. MYSTIC RAPTURE (4) was adequate first-up, got within 2.5 lengths of a subsequent city winner next time out then beaten about the same margin last start. Wide draw could present some issues, but she should be ready for a peak performance. LIMOSA (3) met with support at a massive price first-up ($101 to $71) and ran up to that with a nice third. This looks slightly tougher but will be fitter and the extra 100m suits. YANKEE STREET RAIN (1) is the most experienced runner in the race but achieved a career-best second placing last time out and can go on with it. Debutant BLOW ON THE DICE (8) could bob up after some handy trials.
